module.description: VFocus to compute focus metrics (spec version: 1.00.w.04)

bitfield.description:
\hSelect abs(1-3) or abs(1-5)

Line'1' corresponds to the uppermost line in the 5x1 grid, Line'3' is the middle line and Line'5' is the lowermost line. Therefore, Line'1' is the earliest line clocked out from a sensor point of view assuming the image is being read out from top to bottom

\hHorizontal binning (0 or 2)

If binning is enabled, then the window sizing below follow the post-binning count. Therefore, if the original horizontal count was 32, horizontal binning reduces the count to 16. Now if a window is set as start horizontally at 0 and end at 10, then the settings correspond to the binned frame.

bitenum.description: Average two same color pixels horizontally

Ending position of window 0 in the vertical direction

If the end is programmed as the same value of start, then the window size is treated as 0.
In all cases, the total number of pixels processed is End - Start + 1. Therefore, the minimum window dimension is at least 2.
